-- Taiwan firm to jointly raise 2 bln yuan with Chinese firm
-- 
-- Thu May 22, 2014 05:06AM EDT
-- None



TAIPEI, May 22 (Reuters) - China Development Financial <2883.TW>, parent of Taiwan's largest venture capital firm, said on Thursday it has agreed to tie up with China's Govtor Capital to raise 2 billion yuan ($320.84 million) to invest in mainland firms.

The planned fund would target Chinese firms and those in  energy and environmental protection materials industries, it said in a statement.